comment: The set of positive integers is strictly dominated by the set of real numbers, i.e. the real numbers are uncountable. The proof consists of lemmas ~ ruclem1 through ~ ruclem13 and this final piece. Our proof is based on the proof of Theorem 5.18 of [Truss] p. 114. See ~ ruclem13 for the function existence version of this theorem. For an informal discussion of this proof, see ~ mmcomplex.html#uncountable . For an alternate proof see ~ rucALT . This is Metamath 100 proof #22. (Contributed by NM, 13-Oct-2004.)
